# GitHub API token used to refresh live portfolio data (repo/follower/star
# counts, latest release tags). OPTIONAL: the site works without it, just at the
# lower unauthenticated rate limit (60 req/hr vs 5000 req/hr).
#
# Read ONLY in server code (lib/github.ts) — never exposed to the client bundle.
# Use a fine-grained or classic token with PUBLIC, READ-ONLY scope (no scopes
# are required for public data).
#
# Local: copy this file to `.env.local` and fill it in (gitignored).
# Deploy (Vercel/etc.): set GITHUB_TOKEN as a server-side environment variable.
# CI: the refresh Action uses the built-in secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN automatically.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
